{
  "name": "Greater Barrier",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/protection.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You may fashion your barrier into a flat plane if you so choose. This wall must be contiguous and must begin adjacent to you, although it may extend as far out as close range (if you possess the Distant Protection talent, it must begin within close range and be contained within medium range), and can cover up to 1&#160;10-foot square per caster level. This flat plane may be arranged vertically, horizontally, or along whatever angle you choose. In addition, when creating a barrier, you may spend an additional spell point to increase its Hit Points to 10 per caster level, double its maximum weight, and increase the Break DC by 10. The barrier&#8217;s hit points do not replenish, even if maintained through concentration.</p>\n",
